00:46:30.880 --> 00:46:34.105
If you have to buy this right now
because of the economy

00:46:34.105 --> 00:46:35.955
and money printing, and national debt,

00:46:36.260 --> 00:46:38.564
you'd pay $5,400 for that.

00:46:40.854 --> 00:46:44.855
So you wonder why people worry about
little things like the economy and debt.

00:46:44.855 --> 00:46:46.243
And what I tell people is,

00:46:46.667 --> 00:46:49.200
make a list of what you worry about,

00:46:50.040 --> 00:46:51.850
what are the things
that keep you up at night,

00:46:51.850 --> 00:46:53.978
and then do some preparation for it.

00:46:54.310 --> 00:46:58.335
And what I tell people is that
almost everyone has homeowner's insurance.

00:46:58.335 --> 00:47:02.328
On a scale of 1 to 100,
what chance over the next 12 months

00:47:02.328 --> 00:47:04.140
do you think your house is gonna burn down?

00:47:04.140 --> 00:47:06.550
Almost everyone's
gonna say a one or a two.

00:47:06.550 --> 00:47:09.094
-Not even.
-It's just not even a one or a two.

00:47:09.400 --> 00:47:13.136
Okay. Well, what chance do you think
that we're going to have some type of

00:47:13.136 --> 00:47:14.888
something happen in our country,

00:47:15.190 --> 00:47:18.676
whether it's a COVID-style,
whether it's a Homeland Security attack?

00:47:19.060 --> 00:47:20.630
What percentage do you think?

00:47:20.636 --> 00:47:23.940
So you'll have homeowner's insurance
and you'll have car insurance

00:47:23.940 --> 00:47:25.429
at maybe a one or a two,

00:47:25.749 --> 00:47:27.910
